# Force LF in the repo AND the working tree for all detected-text files.
#
# Why this exists: Sandcastle batches use `branchStrategy: head`, which bind-mounts
# this working tree straight into a Linux container. On Windows (core.autocrlf=true)
# the working tree is CRLF; without this file the container's git (autocrlf=false,
# no attributes) commits those CRLF bytes verbatim, flipping every edited file
# LF->CRLF. `eol=lf` keeps the mounted tree LF, so no batch can reintroduce CRLF.
* text=auto eol=lf
